learning-outcomes:
{'1': 'consolidate and extend your command of Latin grammar and vocabulary;
  to enable you to increase your ability to read Latin with pleasure and
  understanding: some texts at sight, any texts with the aid of dictionaries,
  grammars, translations, and textual notes;', '2': 'develop skills in reading Latin from the study of simplified texts to
  focussed examination of foundational texts of the Greco-Roman world;', '3': 'study these texts against their historical and cultural background; and', '4': 'promote approaches and methodologies for critical thinking not only
  about the ancient sources but also the discourse of our own world.'}
